&lt;p&gt;You’ll work on the product surfaces and systems that drive activation and engagement. That includes building user-facing features, the backend systems that support them, and the instrumentation needed to understand what’s working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a product engineering role. You’ll work across the stack, partner closely with product and design, and ship changes that directly impact how customers experience Thatch.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you will do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and improve core product flows related to onboarding, activation, and enrollment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and ship full stack features, from backend services to user-facing interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instrument product surfaces to understand user behavior and identify opportunities for improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, test, and iterate on changes that improve conversion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with product, design, and cross-functional partners to ship solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to systems that support engagement and lifecycle messaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What we are looking for&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and shipping production web applications across the stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product judgment and comfort working through ambiguity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to reason about user behavior and use data to inform decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning features end-to-end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of cross-functional collaboration and good technical decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care most about the scope you’ve owned, the impact you’ve had, and how you make decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Tools and tech stack&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ruby on Rails.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;React and TailwindCSS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mixpanel, Segment, Braze.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience that stands out&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on onboarding, activation, or engagement-focused product areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at an early-stage or high-growth company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in healthcare, finance, or similarly complex domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;How we work&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We move quickly and are biased toward action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We ship early, learn from real usage, and iterate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We operate with trust, ownership, and high empathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We value clarity over ceremony and quality over shortcuts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What to expect&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to keep the process thoughtful and efficient. Most candidates complete it within about three weeks. You can expect:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An initial conversation with a recruiter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A conversation with the hiring manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative pair programming session, followed by a systems design interview and a separate conversation with one of our engineering managers about how we work together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A final conversation with engineering and company leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
